about.summary: Tree- and rule-based models can be bagged using this package and their predictions equations are stored in an efficient format to reduce the model objects size and speed.

name: r-baguette
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.0.1' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-baguette
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/baguette_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/baguette/baguette_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: e7ede153ba5a49e30f396ee815f6a7a43d5260c6adc5c0117943419998920ed9

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-c50
    - r-butcher
    - r-dials
    - r-dplyr
    - r-earth
    - r-furrr
    - r-generics
    - r-hardhat
    - r-magrittr
    - r-parsnip >=0.1.0
    - r-purrr
    - r-rlang
    - r-rpart
    - r-rsample
    - r-tibble
    - r-tidyr
    - r-withr
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-c50
    - r-butcher
    - r-dials
    - r-dplyr
    - r-earth
    - r-furrr
    - r-generics
    - r-hardhat
    - r-magrittr
    - r-parsnip >=0.1.0
    - r-purrr
    - r-rlang
    - r-rpart
    - r-rsample
    - r-tibble
    - r-tidyr
    - r-withr

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('baguette')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('baguette')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/tidymodels/baguette
  license: MIT
  summary: Tree- and rule-based models can be bagged using this package and their predictions
    equations are stored in an efficient format to reduce the model objects size and
    speed.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT'
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r

# Package: baguette
# Title: Efficient Model Functions for Bagging
# Version: 0.0.1
# Authors@R: c( person( given = "Max", family = "Kuhn", email = "max@rstudio.com", comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-2402-136X"), role = c("aut", "cre") ), person("RStudio", role = "cph") )
# Description: Tree- and rule-based models can be bagged using this package and their predictions equations are stored in an efficient format to reduce the model objects size and speed.
# License: MIT + file LICENSE
# Depends: parsnip (>= 0.1.0)

# URL: https://github.com/tidymodels/baguette

put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
